ck the implications of this decision.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic classloading**\\n\\nI think we need to implement dynamic classloading and catch unsupported errors, but I realize that readClassBytes occurs beforehand. Should I also catch AssertionError? It seems that NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError is probably false. I wonder if it's better to use class bytes from a compile-time string—though it feels a bit messy. Ultimately, that's not really an ideal solution, but I want to make sure we're handling this correctly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_XcFWmrWvoA2sXznkypayTZA0|fc_0cd71c6642117dd20169faa7b8ffa481a098a6dc6b429d63fc", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata -path '*htmlunit-core-js*' -type f | sort | xargs -r grep -n \"ClassFileWriter.class\\|classfile\""}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 584, "output": 1266, "cacheRead": 14336, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 16186, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778034599568, "responseId": "resp_0cd71c6642117dd20169faa7a819dc81a09febfb60227bab99"}}
